-- NFL Unable to Seat 400 Fans at Super Bowl Stadium, Offers $2,700 Refund
-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 2011-02-06T22:57:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-06/nfl-unable-to-seat-400-fans-at-super-bowl-stadium-offers-2-700-refund.html
The  National Football League  was
unable to seat 400 fans who paid $900 for Super Bowl tickets at
Cowboys Stadium in Arlington,  Texas , and was refunding triple
the face value of the seats, the league said in a statement.  The fans were supposed to sit in temporary seats installed
for the game between the Pittsburgh Steelers and  Green Bay
Packers  in an effort to break the attendance record of 103,985.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  